pgTitle: List of international trips made by the President of the United States

rows.text: 19th G7 Summit; Also met with Russian President Boris Yeltsin.
Met with the Presidents and Prime Ministers of the Czech Republic, Hungary, Poland, and Slovakia.
Met with President Boris Yeltsin and senior Russian officials. Signed nuclear disarmament agreement with Ukraine.
Received honorary degree from Oxford University.
Met with the Presidents of the Baltic States.
Addressed the Polish Parliament and attended ceremonies commemorating the Warsaw Ghetto revolt.
20th G7 Summit; Met with the Prime Ministers of Italy, Japan, and Canada. Met with Russian President Boris Yeltsin.
Attended signing of the Israel-Jordan peace agreement and addressed the Jordanian Parliament.
Met with the Amir of Kuwait and addressed U.S. military personnel.
Attended APEC Summit Meeting, followed by State Visit.
Attended transition ceremony for United Nations Mission in Haiti.
Summit meeting. Attended VE Day ceremonies.
21st G7 Summit; Also met with Russian President Boris Yeltsin.
Met with Queen Elizabeth II and Prime Minister John Major; addressed Parliament, and delivered several public addresses in Northern Ireland.
Addressed U.S. military personnel and met with Chancellor Helmut Kohl.
Attended the signing of the Bosnian peace treaty.
Attended the Summit of the Peacemakers.
Discussed cooperation against terrorism with senior Israeli officials.
Met with President Kim Young-sam and proposed four-nation peace talks.
State visit. Issued joint statement on U.S.-Japanese security relations. Addressed the Diet and U.S. Navy personnel.
Attended G-7 summit on nuclear safety and held a summit meeting with President Boris Yeltsin.
Attended a Summit Meeting of Presidents of the Central American Republics.
Partnership for Prosperity and Security in the Caribbean
Attended the signing of the NATO-Russia Founding Act.
Attended U.S.-EU Summit Meeting and commemorated the 50th anniversary of the Marshall Plan.
Stopped en route to and from Bosnia-Herzegovina.
State visit; attended the Second Summit of the Americas.
Met with Chancellor Helmut Kohl; commemorated 50th anniversary of the Berlin Airlift.
Attended WTO meeting commemorating the 50th anniversary of GATT.
Summit meeting with President Boris Yeltsin.
Met with Prime Minister Tony Blair and Northern Irish political leaders; addressed the Northern Ireland Assembly.
Discussed the Kosovo conflict with NATO officials.
Attended Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation Leaders meeting; State visit.
State visit and attended Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe Summit meeting in Istanbul.
Attended conference on Progressive Governance for the 21st Century.
Met with Kosovar Transisional Council; addressed the Albanian community and U.S. military personnel.
Met with President Kocheril Raman Narayanan; signed Joint Statement on Energy and the Environment; addressed the Indian Parliament.
Met with President Hafez al-Assad of Syria.
Attended U.S.-European Union Summit Meeting; met with Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak.
Summit meeting with President Vladimir Putin; addressed the Duma.
Attended the funeral of former Prime Minister Keizō Obuchi.
Briefed President Hosni Mubarak on the Middle East Peace Process.
Met with Taoiseach Bertie Ahern and delivered several public addresses.
Met with Prime Minister Tony Blair and Northern Irish political leaders in Belfast, met with Queen Elizabeth II, and made a speech at the University of Warwick.
